To enforce the types and structure using TypeScript, you can use interfaces or abstract classes. Below are examples of how you can achieve this using both approaches.

### Using an Interface

First, define an interface for the services:

```typescript
interface IChannelServiceDependencies {
    appService: AppService;
}
```

Then, implement this interface in your class:

```typescript
