### Implementing `addToDependencyGraph`
This method would be responsible for updating the dependency graph whenever a service declares a dependency on another service. Here's a basic implementation:

```typescript
private addToDependencyGraph(serviceName: string, dependentServiceName: string) {
    if (!this.dependencyGraph.has(serviceName)) {
        this.dependencyGraph.set(serviceName, new Set());
    }
    this.dependencyGraph.get(serviceName).add(dependentServiceName);
}
```

### Integrating `addToDependencyGraph`
You would call this method in scenarios where dependencies are registered or identified. This could be during the service registration process or specifically when a service is waiting for another service. Heres how you might integrate it:

